docker ps -a
docker-compose up --build
docker exec -it db psql -U postgres
docker exec laravelapp php artisan migrate



Run the Laravel backend container:
docker-compose up laravelapp --no-deps

Run the React frontend container:
docker-compose up frontend --no-deps

Run the PostgreSQL database container:
docker-compose up db --no-deps

Run db and backend:
docker-compose up laravelapp


Running Containers Individually Using 

Run laravel container:
docker run -d --name laravelapp -p 8000:8000 laravelapp:1.0.0

Run react container:
docker run -d --name react-frontend -p 3000:3000 react-frontend:1.0.0

Run Postgres container:
docker run -d --name db -e POSTGRES_USER=postgres -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres -e POSTGRES_DB=postgres -p 5432:5432 postgres:14


Stopping a specific Service:
docker-compose stop <laravelapp // service name>


Stop and remove all containers, networks, and services:
docker compose down -v

Only stop all containers, networks and services:
docker compose down